:css

  body, table, td, th {
    font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', 'Helvetica', 'Arial', sans-serif;
  }

%div#container{dir: "ltr"}
  %h3{style: 'color: #777;'} Peak Load Update
  %h2
    Todayâ€™s Risk of the Annual Peak is
    %span{style: "color: #{risk_color(@report.actual_forecast)}"}
      = @report.actual_forecast.risk.capitalize
  %table{cellspacing: 0, cellpadding: 6, border: 0, style: "border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 8px 0; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 40px; table-layout: fixed;"}
    %thead
      %tr
        - @report.forecasts.each do |f|
          %th{style: "width: 14.29%; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; #{header_style(f)}"}
            - if f.today?
              Today
              %br
            = f.date.to_s(:header)
    %tbody
      %tr
        - @report.forecasts.each do |f|
          %td{style: cell_style(f)}
            - if f.today?
              High of
            = f.high_temp
            &deg;F
      %tr
        - @report.forecasts.each do |f|
          %td{style: cell_style(f)}
            - if f.today?
              Peak load
              %br
            = (f.peak_load.to_f / 1000).round(1)
            GW
            - if f.today?
              %br
              at
              = f.peak_hour.strftime "%l %p"
      %tr
        - @report.forecasts.each do |f|
          %td{style: risk_level_style(f) << 'text-align: center;'}
            PEAK
            = f.risk.upcase

  %hr

  -# FIXME: This belongs in a controller.
  - min_gw = (@config.possible_min.to_f / 1000).round(1)
  - max_gw = (@config.possible_max.to_f / 1000).round(1)

  %h4 Real-Time Data
  %p
    %a{href: 'http://iso-ne.com/isoexpress/', target: '_blank'}
      View the real-time system load graph

  %h4 Reference

  %table{border: 0, width: 400}
    %tr{width: 200}
      %td
        %strong{style: 'color: green;'} UNLIKELY
      %td
        &lt; #{ min_gw } GW
    %tr
      %td
        %strong{style: 'color: orange;'} POSSIBLE
      %td
        #{ min_gw } GW &mdash; #{ max_gw } GW
    %tr
      %td
        %strong{style: 'color: red;'} LIKELY
      %td
        &gt; #{ max_gw } GW

  %h4 How to use this table
  %p
    The following table is intended as a guide to help entities anticipate when the annual peak load for the ISO-NE system2 will occur and to make their own decisions about whether and when to load shed.
  %p
    The "Risk of the Annual Peak" rating is generated by MAPC based on a comparison of the estimated Peak Load for the day reported by ISO-NE and load on historic annual peak days.
    %strong
      It is a recommendation only.
  %p
    This service, provided by MAPC, is intended for municipal and commercial facility operators that will use it to manage their building energy use. For
